data.text:
Billups not likely to make Nuggets debut tonight at Golden State Chauncey Billups

The Nuggets said Tuesday Billups didn’t have enough time to get to the Bay Area. He was in Charlotte with the Pistons when the deal took place.

Denver acquired Billups, a point guard and Denver native, along with Antonio McDyess and Cheikh Samb from Detroit on Monday in exchange for Allen Iverson.

Billups will likely play in his first game for the Nuggets on Friday night when they host Dallas.

Suns’ Tucker sidelined

Alando Tucker Thomas Carter

Tucker, in his second season, has not been part of new coach Terry Porter’s regular rotation.

By The Associated Press
